				\begin{document}
$$ p(x)={Cx}^{-\alpha} $$
\end{document}px=Cx−αwhere p(x) decreases as x increases and α is a coefficient indicating the level of decrease. Also, C is a constant to make the maximum value of cumulative probability function to be 1. C = ec, and it can be expressed without the negative sign. However, the negative sign is used in general to indicate clearly that the graph has a decreasing shape toward the end.

